Bias

Some genes will be more likely to be identified as significant than others. And significance is defined by the overlap to a DMR. A DMR requires at least 3 CpGs identified as significant. Therefore logically, a gene that overlaps more CpGs could be expected to be more likely to overlap a DMR. That gene would also likely be longer. This is what we wish to visualise.
